snippet.textDisplay:
PLEASE READ STEVE:
Hi Steve I've been watching your show since forever. Introduced via my kids and the fact that we have a very old black female cat who would be a match made in heaven for Sylvester. I'm shouting out to you today after listening to your outro. I suffer exactly as you describe. In fact I wanted to create a channel back yonder but knew I wouldn't be reliable enough. It's affected many things in my life especially work life. So to see the extremely witty and talented work you do is amazing. Don't worry about how long in between uploads you have just keep it up because selfishly it's one of the few things I get a kick out of on You Tube. Sometimes when I'm in a funk I look at work I've done and wonder 'did I do that' cos I can't believe where the energy and I guess, talent/ inspiration came from! You truly are talented though. I thought you might work in the TV industry or similar. Just remember many out there know how you feel and you're inspirational (to me, and I'm sure many others). I'm off to check out that green "Die" hoodie. My cat "Sooty" has even mustered up a reluctant "hi Sylvester" as she is such a bundle of joy!!!!!! 💖🐱🐾
